> {{#get "posts" filter="tag:TEST"}}
> {{#get "posts" filter="slug:TEST"}}

It's not only about relational slugs, it's about **any slug query using uppercase notation**.

in gh-profile-image, within the imageBackground property declaration I am accessing the configuration variable via 

    this.get('config.useGravatar');

Is that correct? It is returning undefined in gh-profile-image-test but true during normal usage

Looking through the current master for Selectize, it looks like there's no current way to disable the auto-complete on return functionality:

```
case KEY_RETURN:
    if (self.isOpen && self.$activeOption) {
        self.onOptionSelect({currentTarget: self.$activeOption});
        e.preventDefault();
    }
    return;
```

There's also no issue open for that enhancement at the moment.

@shawntoffel thanks for the bug report, we used to have a 1 day session length, so this was pretty accurate, but now that we've increased the session length you're spot on that the "last seen date" is no longer a good reflection of reality.

We need to find a new way to update this, which keeps the balance of not updating the user model too frequently (because it's just not that useful at the moment) but also accurately reflects that the user has been online. 

Perhaps token refreshes (which happen once per hour, I believe) would be a good option?

Same thing happened to me. 

